---
import GitHubGraph from './GitHubGraph.astro';
---

<section id="about" class="about section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="about__title">About</h2>
    <div class="about__content">
      <p>
        I build software mostly alone, spec-first, and I like it that way. Started 
        <strong>The Cinder Project</strong> - a personal ecosystem of auditable, transparency-first 
        open source tools spanning systems programming, backends, and frontend.
      </p>
      <p>
        Learning CTF/HTB and pentesting, which shows up in how I think about the things I build.
        Daily driving EndeavourOS (I use Arch BTW).
      </p>
    </div>
    <GitHubGraph />
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .about__title {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .about__content {
    max-width: 700px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .about__content p {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
</style>